            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>In nomine Domini salvatoris nostri Iesu Christi Dei eterni. <persName
                            key="#Princeps" ref="#people/3019">Robbertus</persName> divina ordinante
                        clementia Capuanorum <rs key="#Princeps">princeps</rs> petitioni dilectorum
                        suorum baronum clementer favet. Nos Robbertus divina ordinante clementia
                        Capuanorum princeps notum fieri volumus universis huius sancte catholice
                        Ecclesie cunctisque baronibus ac militibus fidelibusque nostris quoniam nos,
                        quem divina clementia commovit in principem ut ecclesiarum Dei ditator atque
                        defensor existam, et specialiter <orgName key="#Monasteries"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/84">Casinensis</orgName>
                        <rs key="#Monasteries">monasterii</rs>, cuius nobis defensio atque tutela
                        commissa est, predecessorum nostrorum <rs key="#Vir_gloriosus/vir_sublimis"
                            >gloriosorum</rs>
                        <rs key="#Princeps">principum</rs> exempla sequentes, que idem monasterium
                        exaltare ac multis opibus ditare studuerunt, nos quoque in quantum possumus
                        idem facere properamus. Igitur ad salutem et remedium animarum quondam
                        gloriosorum principum, <persName
                            key="#Princeps #Vir_gloriosus/vir_sublimis #grandparentOf"
                            ref="#people/3001">Richardus</persName> scilicet <rs
                            key="#grandparentOf">avi</rs> ac <persName
                            key="#Princeps #Vir_gloriosus/vir_sublimis #parentOf" ref="#people/3002"
                            >Iordani</persName>
                        <rs key="#parentOf">patris</rs> necnon <persName
                            key="#Princeps #Vir_gloriosus/vir_sublimis #siblingOf"
                            ref="#people/3010">secundi Richardi</persName>
                        <rs key="#siblingOf">fratris</rs> nostri, ac ob statum nostri principatus,
                            <rs key="#Intercessory">interventu</rs> quoque domni <persName
                            key="#Intercessory #Bishops #Personal_rank" ref="#people/4218"
                            >Pandulfi</persName>
                        <rs key="#Personal_rank">venerabilis</rs>
                        <rs key="#Bishops">episcopi</rs>
                        <placeName ref="#places/174">Teanensis</placeName> et nostrorum dilectorum
                        baronum, videlicet <persName key="#Intercessory"><name
                                ref="Richardus fil. Bartholomaei">Richardi filii
                            Bartholomei</name></persName> et <persName
                            key="#Intercessory #Consul/hypatos" ref="#people/4219">Leonis</persName>
                        <placeName ref="#places/2855">Fundani</placeName>
                        <rs key="#Consul/hypatos">consulis</rs> et <persName key="#Intercessory"
                                ><name ref="Thomas de Calvi">Thome de Calvo</name></persName> ac
                            <persName ref="#people/3040" key="#Intercessory">Ugoni de
                            Pulita</persName>, per hoc videlicet principale scriptum in perpetuum
                        damus, tradimus, concedimus ac confirmamus prefato monasterio Sancti
                        Benedicti et <rs key="#Personal_rank">venerabili</rs> domno <persName
                            key="#Abbots #Personal_rank" ref="#people/4216">Girardo</persName>
                        eiusdem monasterii <rs key="#Abbots">abbati</rs> omnibusque suis
                        successoribus, <rs key="#Castle">castrum</rs> silicet qui vocatur <placeName
                            key="#Rivers #Mountains #Landed_possessions #Forests #Hay/fodder #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Coloni/tenants #Castle #Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters"
                            ref="#places/4526">Suio</placeName> cum <rs key="#Coloni/tenants"
                            >hominibus</rs> et <rs key="#Landed_possessions">terris cultis et
                            incultis</rs>, planis, <rs key="#Mountains">montibus</rs>, <rs
                            key="#Forests">silvis</rs>, <rs
                            key="#Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters"><rs key="#Hay/fodder"
                                >pascuis</rs>, aquis</rs>, <rs
                            key="#Rivers #Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters">aquarum
                            decursibus</rs> et cum omnibus eiusdem castri pertinentiis, sicuti
                            <persName ref="#people/3075">Richardus de Aquila</persName> et <persName
                            key="#childOf" ref="#people/4220">Andreas</persName>
                        <rs key="#childOf">filius</rs> eius tenuerunt illud octo dies antequam
                        mortui essent, ad possessionem et potestatem et dominationem ipsius
                        monasterii et memorati domni Girardi venerabili abbati et omnium successorum
                        eius, faciendi de eorum castro et de tota eius pertinentia ut prediximus,
                        utilitatem ipsius monasterii, remota omni inquietudine, contrarietate et
                        molestia nostra et omnium principum et successorum nostrorum vel principum,
                        comitum vel vicecomitum, iudicum, sculdaorum, castaldeorum aliorumque
                        hominum mortalium persone. Quod siquis huius nostre concessionis et
                        confirmationis pagine contemptor aut violator extiterit, aut contra hoc
                        principale scriptum agere presumpserit, <rs key="#Penalty">mille libras auri
                            purissimi</rs> persolvat, medietatem iam nominato monasterio Sancti
                        Benedicti et prephato domno Girardo venerabili abbati et successoribus eius,
                        et medietatem nostro sacro Capuano Palatio, et soluta pena librarum auri hoc
                        principale scriptum cum omnibus que et qualiter continet firmum ac
                        inviolabile maneat imperpetuum. Et ut firmius credatur et diligentius ab
                        omnibus observetur, manu propria illud corroboravimus et nostri sigilli
                        inpressione iussimus insigniri. Signum domini <persName
                            key="#Princeps #Vir_magnificus #Vir_gloriosus/vir_sublimis"
                            ref="#people/3019">Robberti</persName>
                        <rs key="#Vir_gloriosus/vir_sublimis">gloriosissimi</rs> ac <rs
                            key="#Vir_magnificus">magnifici</rs> principis. ROBBERTVS. Ex iussione
                        prephate serenissime potestatis scripsi ego <persName key="#Writer #Judge"
                            ref="#people/3012">Quiriacus</persName>
                        <rs key="#Judge">palatinus iudex</rs> in anno dominice incarnationis
                        millesimo centesimo septimo decimo, et decimo anno principatus prephati
                        domni Robberti gloriosi principis Capue. Data in <placeName key="#Cities"
                            ref="#places/173">Capuana</placeName>
                        <rs key="#Cities">civitate</rs> mense Februario per indictionem decimam. </ab>
